@node Actions ü™Ñ
@section Actions ü™Ñ

Actions add behavior to your content.  They can be configured per-slide and in some cases per-element.

There are two kinds of actions:
@itemize
@item
@samp{Section actions}: work on the content in the heading's section.  They use the @code{dslide-action} base class and prefix.
@item
@samp{Slide actions}: display the slide@comma{} usually by narrowing@comma{} and then handle the child headings@comma{} either inline or as independent slides.  They use the @code{dslide-slide-action} base class and prefix.
@end itemize

To browse all actions@comma{} because they are all EIEIO classes@comma{} you can use @code{eieio-browse} and see the actions descend from @code{dslide-action}.
@example
+--dslide-stateful-sequence
     +--dslide-action
          +--dslide-action-propertize
          +--dslide-action-image
          +--dslide-action-babel
          +--dslide-action-kmacro
          +--dslide-action-item-reveal
          +--dslide-action-hide-markup
          +--dslide-slide-action
               +--dslide-slide-action-every-child
               +--dslide-slide-action-inline
               +--dslide-slide-action-child
               +--dslide-slide-action-flat
@end example

