@node Per-Element
@subsection Per-Element

Some actions@comma{} such as @code{dslide-action-propertize}@comma{} can't decide which elements to operate on or what to do with those elements.  They are both enabled and configured per-element by using an @strong{affiliated keyword}.

@example
#+attr_dslide_propertize: face '(:foreground "#ff0000")
This text will be red
@end example

üöß This is the preferred style of configuration moving forward.

‚ÑπÔ∏è Affiliated keywords @emph{must} have the @samp{attr} prefix or they will not apply to the content they precede.  Affiliated keywords cannot be attached to headings@comma{} which must use their property drawer to attach data.

@node Keyword
@subsection Keyword

For some actions@comma{} the configuration @emph{is} the content.  They use a keyword.  The value of the keyword is the content for the action.  As elsewhere@comma{} use plist @samp{:key value} style configuration.
@example
#+dslide_kmacro: :keys "M-x a n i m a t e <return>"
@end example

@node Property Drawer
@subsection Property Drawer

Some actions run on every element of the heading before you even see the content.  Since there may be no associated content to attach them to@comma{} they can only be configured in the property drawer.  Slide actions are always configured this way.
@example
* Inline Children
:PROPERTIES:
:DSLIDE_SLIDE_ACTION: dslide-slide-action-child :header nil
:DSLIDE_ACTIONS: dslide-action-item-reveal :inline t
:END:
- You won't believe these animations
- This is the world's greatest presentation software
  + But mainly because it integrates with all you programming tools
@end example
@itemize
@item
@samp{DSLIDE_SLIDE_ACTION}: Accepts one slide action and its @samp{:key value} configuration
@item
@samp{DSLIDE_ACTIONS:} Can be used to list multiple action classes and their @samp{:key value} configurations.
@end itemize

The @code{dslide-action-hide-markup} action only runs when entering a slide@comma{} to hide markup before you see anything. üöß It will be configurable in the property drawer.  Right now it checks @code{dslide-hide-markup-types}.

üöß These actions can currently only be configured in the property drawer but will be configured mainly per-element where possible in 0.7.0:

@itemize
@item
@code{dslide-action-image}
@item
@code{dslide-action-item-reveal}
@end itemize

