@section Configuring Actions üéõÔ∏è

Many actions understand configuration options@comma{} allowing tuning of similar behaviors from the same class.

üí° To view an action's default values@comma{} call @code{describe-symbol} on it.  Any slot definition usually has the same @samp{:initarg} and will be understood when used in the configuration.

Configuring is usually done by adding plist-style @samp{:key value} arguments after the class name@comma{} keyword@comma{} or affiliated keyword:
@example
* A Headline For a Heading
:PROPERTIES:
# configuration after a class name
:DSLIDE_ACTIONS: dslide-action-item-reveal :inline t
:END:

# A keyword configuration
