üÜí The jitter uses a Laplace distribution to sample a perturbation power.  This power is mapped onto the zero-to-infinity factor range by raising e to the power of jitter.  This is multiplied by @samp{:frequency}@comma{} which is a duration.  As a result@comma{} while the jitter is usually pretty small@comma{} it does have some wild variation@comma{} which does look a bit more human.

